pub.citation: Ro, K-E., C. S. Keener, B. A. McPheron. 1997. Molecular Phylogenetic Study of the Ranunculaceae: Utility of the Nuclear 26S Ribosomal DNA in Inferring Intrafamilial Relationships. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evoltuion 8(2): 117-127.

pmmd.notes: Ranunculaceae relationships inferred from maximum parsimony analysis. The tree is a strict consensus tree of the 20 most parsimonious trees. Numbers indicate bootstrap P values higher than 50% (825 replications). Statistics of each most parsimonious tree: length 5 510; CI 5 0.494; HI 5 0.506; RI 5 0.651; RC 5 0.322.
